    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Clara H. Waite was state regent of the Michigan Daughters of the American Revolution. She and her husband William H. Wait, a professor of German and other modern languages at the University of Michigan traveled extensively and were engaged in the social life of Ann Arbor.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The Clara Hadley Wait collection includes scrapbooks, notebooks on art, travel journals, DAR materials, and photograph albums. The scrapbooks contain newspaper clippings, correspondence, copies of her articles, and other materials relating primarily to her civic activities, including description of her activities with the D.A.R. during World War I. The collection includes a European travel diary, 1893, of her husband, William H. Wait.</p>
    </scopecontent>
